## 📈 Phase 5: Evaluation & Explainability

**Goal:** Deep evaluation with confusion matrix, ROC curves, and SHAP analysis.

### How Model Accuracy is Calculated

#### Accuracy Formula

$$Accuracy = \frac{TP + TN}{TP + TN + FP + FN}$$

**Our Confusion Matrix (Logistic Regression):**

```
                  Predicted
                No      Yes
Actual No    [ 70  |   12 ]    → Specificity: 70/(70+12) = 85.4%
Actual Yes   [  8  |   94 ]    → Sensitivity: 94/(94+8) = 92.2%
```

$$Accuracy = \frac{94 + 70}{94 + 70 + 12 + 8} = \frac{164}{184} = 89.1\%$$

#### All Key Metrics Explained

| Metric | Formula | Our Value | What It Means |
|--------|---------|-----------|---------------|
| **Accuracy** | (TP+TN) / Total | 89.1% | Overall correct predictions |
| **Precision** | TP / (TP+FP) | 94/(94+12) = 88.7% | Of those flagged HD, how many truly have it |
| **Recall (Sensitivity)** | TP / (TP+FN) | 94/(94+8) = **92.2%** | Of actual HD patients, how many we catch |
| **F1 Score** | 2 × (P×R)/(P+R) | **0.904** | Harmonic mean of precision & recall |
| **Specificity** | TN / (TN+FP) | 70/(70+12) = 85.4% | Of healthy patients, how many correctly cleared |
| **AUC-ROC** | Area under ROC curve | **0.933** | Overall discriminative ability (0.5=random, 1.0=perfect) |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> In medicine, **Recall is more important than Precision.** Missing a heart disease patient (FN=8) is far more dangerous than a false alarm (FP=12). Our model prioritizes catching sick patients.

![Confusion Matrices](file:///C:/Users/mmddf/.gemini/antigravity/brain/114a5bdb-9aad-4662-aa11-2feb9fb16cb8/chart_12_cell31.png)

### ROC Curve — What It Means

The ROC (Receiver Operating Characteristic) curve plots **True Positive Rate vs False Positive Rate** at every classification threshold.

- **AUC = 1.0:** Perfect model
- **AUC = 0.5:** Random guessing (diagonal line)
- **Our AUC = 0.933:** Excellent discriminative power

